Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.00,0:00:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,｢There was a hungry crow｣
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.00,0:00:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,｢Who wanted to get some feed｣
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.00,0:00:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,｢If only this beak were a little longer｣
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.00,0:00:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,｢That feed would be a bit closer｣
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.00,0:01:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,｢A crow can think｣
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.00,0:01:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,｢can think... can think｣
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.00,0:01:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Observe, propose a hypothesis, then experiment and consider results.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.00,0:01:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Learn the way of scientific thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.00,0:01:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We begin with a Thinking Observation
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.00,0:01:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Look closely at the sand in this aquarium.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.00,0:01:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all stripey.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.00,0:01:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's separated into three colors, like geological strata.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.00,0:01:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is it separated into these colors?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.00,0:01:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If we look at it the next morning...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.00,0:01:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The stripes are gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.00,0:02:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The sand is all a uniform color.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.00,0:02:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on here?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.00,0:02:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's try looking at it at the original time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.00,0:02:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If we look at it at night again we see the sand separated into 3 colors.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.00,0:02:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It only comes out at night?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.00,0:02:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,As a test, let's poke the sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.00,0:02:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Hunh? When we move the sand...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.00,0:02:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the layers underneath move with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.00,0:02:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If we pile it up, the layers underneath also pile up.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.00,0:02:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Why should this be?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.00,0:02:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's try observing for a little while.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.00,0:03:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Ahh. We can see somethig beneath the hermit crab.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.00,0:03:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Something like a shadow.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.00,0:03:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is being cast on the lower layers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.00,0:03:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this some kind of shadow?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.00,0:03:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's try testing with a pair of tweezers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.00,0:03:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When we lower it into the water
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.00,0:03:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,as we thought, something like a shadow is cast.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.00,0:03:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This shadow like thing
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.00,0:03:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,might it have something to do with the light illuminating the aquarium?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.00,0:03:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's try turnig the light off.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.00,0:03:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The stripes disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.00,0:04:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's try moving the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.00,0:04:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The stripes moved.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.00,0:04:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,As we thought, this light is the true cause of the stripes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.00,0:04:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But as we think further it seems a bit strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.00,0:04:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When the light shines on these tweezers
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.00,0:04:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The shadow ought only be cast onto this desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.00,0:04:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet somehow a shadow appears in the sand?
