Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.00,0:06:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Today's problem deals with this triangular stand and a ball bearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.00,0:06:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This triangular stand is placed on a scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.00,0:06:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a rail attached to this stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.00,0:06:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a little tape attached at the top of the rail.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.00,0:06:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,firmly fixing the ball in place.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.00,0:06:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When the ball is sitting there...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.00,0:06:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it's exactly 200 grams.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.00,0:06:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The weight of the ball and the stand together.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.00,0:06:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now this is the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.00,0:06:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,A short time later the ball will come off the tape
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.00,0:06:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it will begin rolling.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.00,0:07:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,While the ball is rolling down this incline
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.00,0:07:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,what will happen to the displayed weight?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.21,0:07:27.66,white-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(130,89)}1. The weight will increase.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.94,0:07:27.66,white-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(167,144)}2. The weight will remain at 200 grams
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.61,0:07:27.66,white-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(132,198)}3. The weight will decrease.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.00,0:07:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what will happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.00,0:07:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll present the answer at the end of the program.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.00,0:07:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, please think hard about it, won't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.00,0:07:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Observation, hypothesis, experiment and reflection.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.00,0:07:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Thinking scientifically. Thinking Crow.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.00,0:08:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And now the answer from earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.40,0:08:18.44,black-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(304,111)}Q: When the Ball starts to roll what will happen to the weight on the scale?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.93,0:08:18.44,black-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(375,197)}1. The weight will increase.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.44,0:08:18.44,black-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(414,247)}2. The weight will remain at 200 grams.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.54,0:08:18.44,black-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(379,292)}3. The weight will decrease.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.00,0:08:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, did you think about it carefully?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.00,0:08:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, let's try it for real.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.00,0:08:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We affix the ball to the tape and remove our hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.00,0:08:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We wait for the ball to come free from the tape on its own and start rolling.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.00,0:08:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if I touched it even a small amount
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.00,0:08:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the indicated weight would easily change.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.00,0:08:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, what will to the weight?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.00,0:08:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Please look closely at the weight shown on the scale, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.00,0:09:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Did it change?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.00,0:09:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's look at that one more time
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.00,0:09:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the answer...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.00,0:09:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you think this is?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.00,0:09:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When the ball is held by the tape...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.00,0:09:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The weight of the ball is entirely contributed to this stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.00,0:09:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But when the ball is rolling...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.00,0:09:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,From here on we think for ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.00,0:09:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,From here on we're all thinking crows.
